301.definition: [Ἀμώς] of Hebrew origin ({{H531}}); Amos, an Israelite

302.definition: [ἄν] a primary particle, denoting a supposition, wish, possibility or uncertainty Usually unexpressed except by the subjunctive or potential mood. Also contracted for {{G1437}}.

303.definition: [ἀνά] a primary preposition and adverb; properly, up; but (by extension) used (distributively) severally, or (locally) at (etc.) In compounds (as a prefix) it often means (by implication) repetition, intensity, reversal, etc.

305.definition: [ἀναβαίνω] from {{G303}} and the base of {{G939}}; to go up (literally or figuratively)

306.definition: [ἀναβάλλομαι] middle voice from {{G303}} and {{G906}}; to put off (for oneself)

307.definition: [ἀναβιβάζω] from {{G303}} and a derivative of the base of {{G939}}; to cause to go up, i.e. haul (a net)

308.definition: [ἀναβλέπω] from {{G303}} and {{G991}}; to look up; by implication, to recover sight

312.definition: [ἀναγγέλλω] from {{G303}} and the base of {{G32}}; to announce (in detail)

313.definition: [ἀναγεννάω] from {{G303}} and {{G1080}}; to beget or (by extension) bear (again)

314.definition: [ἀναγινώσκω] from {{G303}} and {{G1097}}; to know again, i.e. (by extension) to read

316.definition: [ἀναγκαῖος] from {{G318}}; necessary; by implication, close (of kin)

317.definition: [ἀναγκαστῶς] adverb from a derivative of {{G315}}; compulsorily

318.definition: [ἀνάγκη] from {{G303}} and the base of {{G43}}; constraint (literally or figuratively); by implication, distress

319.definition: [ἀναγνωρίζομαι] middle voice from {{G303}} and {{G1107}}; to make (oneself) known

321.definition: [ἀνάγω] from {{G303}} and {{G71}}; to lead up; by extension to bring out; specially, to sail away

322.definition: [ἀναδείκνυμι] from {{G303}} and {{G1166}}; to exhibit, i.e. (by implication) to indicate, appoint

324.definition: [ἀναδέχομαι] from {{G303}} and {{G1209}}; to entertain (as a guest)

326.definition: [ἀναζάω] from {{G303}} and {{G2198}}; to recover life (literally or figuratively)

329.definition: [ἀναζωπυρέω] from {{G303}} and a compound of the base of {{G2226}} and {{G4442}}; to re-enkindle

330.definition: [ἀναθάλλω] from {{G303}} and θάλλω (to flourish); to revive

331.definition: [ἀνάθεμα] from {{G394}}; a (religious) ban or (concretely) excommunicated (thing or person)

332.definition: [ἀναθεματίζω] from {{G331}}; to declare or vow under penalty of execration

333.definition: [ἀναθεωρέω] from {{G303}} and {{G2334}}; to look again (i.e. attentively) at (literally or figuratively)

334.definition: [ἀνάθημα] from {{G394}} (like {{G331}}, but in a good sense); a votive offering

335.definition: [ἀναίδεια] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle (compare {{G427}})) and {{G127}}; impudence, i.e. (by implication) importunity

337.definition: [ἀναιρέω] from {{G303}} and (the active of) {{G138}}; to take up, i.e. adopt; by implication, to take away (violently), i.e. abolish, murder

338.definition: [ἀναίτιος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G159}} (in the sense of {{G156}}); innocent

339.definition: [ἀνακαθίζω] from {{G303}} and {{G2523}}; properly, to set up, i.e. (reflexively) to sit up

340.definition: [ἀνακαινίζω] from {{G303}} and a derivative of {{G2537}}; to restore

341.definition: [ἀνακαινόω] from {{G303}} and a derivative of {{G2537}}; to renovate

343.definition: [ἀνακαλύπτω] from {{G303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{G2572}}; to unveil

345.definition: [ἀνακεῖμαι] from {{G303}} and {{G2749}}; to recline (as a corpse or at a meal)

346.definition: [ἀνακεφαλαίομαι] from {{G303}} and {{G2775}} (in its original sense); to sum up

348.definition: [ἀνακόπτω] from {{G303}} and {{G2875}}; to beat back, i.e. check

350.definition: [ἀνακρίνω] from {{G303}} and {{G2919}}; properly, to scrutinize, i.e. (by implication) investigate, interrogate, determine

352.definition: [ἀνακύπτω] from {{G303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{G2955}}; to unbend, i.e. rise; figuratively, be elated

355.definition: [ἀναλίσκω] from {{G303}} and a form of the alternate of {{G138}}; properly, to use up, i.e. destroy

356.definition: [ἀναλογία] from a compound of {{G303}} and {{G3056}}; proportion

357.definition: [ἀναλογίζομαι] middle voice from {{G356}}; to estimate, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate

358.definition: [ἄναλος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G251}}; saltless, i.e. insipid

360.definition: [ἀναλύω] from {{G303}} and {{G3089}}; to break up, i.e. depart (literally or figuratively)

361.definition: [ἀναμάρτητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G264}}; sinless

363.definition: [ἀναμιμνήσκω] from {{G303}} and {{G3403}}; to remind; (reflexively) to recollect

365.definition: [ἀνανεόω] from {{G303}} and a derivative of {{G3501}}; to renovate, i.e. reform

366.definition: [ἀνανήφω] from {{G303}} and {{G3525}}; to become sober again, i.e. (figuratively) regain (one's) senses

367.definition: [Ἀνανίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H2608}}); Ananias, the name of three Israelites

368.definition: [ἀναντίῤῥητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of {{G473}} and {{G4483}}; indisputable

370.definition: [ἀνάξιος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G514}}; unfit

373.definition: [ἀναπαύω] from {{G303}} and {{G3973}}; (reflexively) to repose (literally or figuratively (be exempt), remain); by implication, to refresh

375.definition: [ἀναπέμπω] from {{G303}} and {{G3992}}; to send up or back

376.definition: [ἀνάπηρος] from {{G303}} (in the sense of intensity) and πῆρος (maimed); crippled

377.definition: [ἀναπίπτω] from {{G303}} and {{G4098}}; to fall back, i.e. lie down, lean back

378.definition: [ἀναπληρόω] from {{G303}} and {{G4137}}; to complete; by implication, to occupy, supply; figuratively, to accomplish (by coincidence ot obedience)

379.definition: [ἀναπολόγητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G626}}; indefensible

380.definition: [ἀναπτύσσω] from {{G303}} (in the sense of reversal) and {{G4428}}; to unroll (a scroll or volume)

382.definition: [ἀναρίθμητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G705}}; unnumbered, i.e. without number

384.definition: [ἀνασκευάζω] from {{G303}} (in the sense of reversal) and a derivative of {{G4632}}; properly, to pack up (baggage), i.e. (by implication, and figuratively) to upset

385.definition: [ἀνασπάω] from {{G303}} and {{G4685}}; to take up or extricate

386.definition: [ἀνάστασις] from {{G450}}; a standing up again, i.e. (literally) a resurrection from death (individual, genitive case or by implication, (its author)), or (figuratively) a (moral) recovery (of spiritual truth)

387.definition: [ἀναστατόω] from a derivative of {{G450}} (in the sense of removal); properly, to drive out of home, i.e. (by implication) to disturb (literally or figuratively)

390.definition: [ἀναστρέφω] from {{G303}} and {{G4762}}; to overturn; also to return; by implication, to busy oneself, i.e. remain, live

392.definition: [ἀνατάσσομαι] from {{G303}} and the middle voice of {{G5021}}; to arrange

393.definition: [ἀνατέλλω] from {{G303}} and the base of {{G5056}}; to (cause to) arise

394.definition: [ἀνατίθεμαι] from {{G303}} and the middle voice of {{G5087}}; to set forth (for oneself), i.e propound

395.definition: [ἀνατολή] from {{G393}}; a rising of light, i.e. dawn (figuratively); by implication, the east (also in plural)

396.definition: [ἀνατρέπω] from {{G303}} and the base of {{G5157}}; to overturn (figuratively)

397.definition: [ἀνατρέφω] from {{G303}} and {{G5142}}; to rear (physically or mentally)

398.definition: [ἀναφαίνω] from {{G303}} and {{G5316}}; to show, i.e. (reflexively) appear, or (passively) to have pointed out

399.definition: [ἀναφέρω] from {{G303}} and {{G5342}}; to take up (literally or figuratively)
